Bridgepoint Rises After Being Named Best Stock Pick

-- B y   S a i j e l   K i s h a n   a n d   J o s h   F i n e m a n
-- 
2011-05-25T20:24:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/bridgepoint-rises-after-being-named-best-investment-idea-1-.html
(Corrects name of contest winner in third paragraph.)  Bridgepoint Education Inc. (BPI)  rose the
most in more than six months after the company was picked as the
best investment idea at the Ira Sohn conference today in New
York.  Bridgepoint gained as much as 15 percent, the most since
Nov. 2, and rose $2.37, or 12 percent, to $22.84 at 3:40 p.m. in
New York Stock Exchange composite trading.  Sunjay Gorawara, a 21-year-old business and finance student
at  Indiana University  who submitted Bridgepoint to the contest,
said he expects the stock to rise to $47 in the coming year. He
is due to start next month at JPMorgan Chase & Co. as an analyst
in the investment banking division  To contact the reporters on this story:
